[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmp_jrql_kk[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libFuzzer run of the `exif_from_data_fuzzer` harness triggered an [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow in the `exif_get_sshort` function of the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibexif library. During processing of a malformed EXIF data block, the code [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempted to read one byte past the end of a [0m[1;36m512[0m[39m-byte heap allocation. The overflow[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmanifests when handling Apple maker-note data via the `exif_mnote_data_apple_load` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  An AddressSanitizer report indicates a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte out-of-bounds read in [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_get_sshort` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `libexif/exif-utils.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The offending access is [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m bytes [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbeyond a [0m[1;36m512[0m[39m-byte buffer that was allocated to hold EXIF segment data.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability Type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  This is a heap-buffer-overflow: reading past the end of an allocated heap buffer.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Key Observations  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The vulnerability is detected in production code [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlibexif[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, not in the fuzz [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mharness itself.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The overflow is triggered in the Apple maker-note processing path [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`exif_mnote_data_apple_load`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m after reading a signed short from the input.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The buffer is allocated just prior to the fuzzer callback and populated by [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_new_from_data`. The read occurs when utilities attempt to interpret [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmulti-byte fields without verifying bounds.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The error surfaces under AddressSanitizer in a single run of the fuzzer with a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcustom input [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Relevant Code Areas for Investigation  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. **libexif/exif-utils.c**  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Function: `exif_get_sshort` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand its caller `exif_get_short`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Boundaries checks around reads from the data buffer  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. **libexif/apple/exif-mnote-data-apple.c**  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Function: `exif_mnote_data_apple_load`  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – How offsets and lengths are computed for maker-note fields  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. **libexif/exif-data.c**  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Buffer allocation for EXIF data [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_data_new_from_data`, [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Any assumptions about minimum buffer size vs. data offsets  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. **Fuzzer Entry Point**  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – `exif_from_data_fuzzer.cc` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mto understand how the data buffer is passed in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand whether any initial length checks exist[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA review of these modules will provide a holistic view of how EXIF data lengths and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffsets are validated [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor not[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m before multi-byte reads, and will help confirm the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprecise conditions under which the out-of-bounds access occurs.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is an AddressSanitizer-detected heap-buffer-overflow in libexif’s[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mApple MakerNote reader [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_mnote_data_apple_load`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, where the code reads a [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msigned short at `buf + ofs + [0m[1;36m14[0m[39m` without sufficient bounds checks. A patch was [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempted that:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Checks that `buf_size` is at least `ofs + [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m` before reading the entry count.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Reads the count via `exif_get_sshort`, rejects negative values, and casts to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`unsigned int`.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adds a second check ensuring `buf_size` can contain all `tcount` entries [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;36m6[0m[39m` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes each[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m plus [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the fuzzer run still crashes at the same [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_get_sshort` call—indicating that the new pre-checks do not fully cover the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mout-of-bounds read.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Initial Issue**  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer invocation [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_from_data_fuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m exercised [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_new_from_data`, which led into `exif_mnote_data_apple_load`.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `exif-mnote-data-apple.c`, the code unconditionally calls  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     tcount = [0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned int[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35mexif_get_short[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf + ofs + [0m[1;36m14[0m[39m, d->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     without verifying that `buf + ofs + [0m[1;36m14[0m[39m` lies within the allocated `buf_size`. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer reports a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte read past the end of a [0m[1;36m512[0m[39m-byte allocation:[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     READ of size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m at [0m[1;36m0x515000000785[0m[39m thread T0[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m … exif_get_sshort[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m … exif_get_short [0m[35m/[0m[95mexif-utils.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m104[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m … exif_mnote_data_apple_load [0m[35m/apple/[0m[95mexif-mnote-data-apple.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m110[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     …[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m0x515000000785[0m[39m is located [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m bytes after [0m[1;36m512[0m[39m-byte region [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x[0m[39m…[0m[1;36m580[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x[0m[39m…[0m[1;36m780[0m[1;39m)[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The failure reveals that neither the maker-note header parsing nor the entry [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcount check guarded the read.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Patch Attempt**  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `libexif/apple/exif-mnote-data-apple.c`, the block around line [0m[1;36m82[0m[39m was [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrewritten. The patch:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Introduces a check `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf_size < ofs + [0m[1;36m16[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` before any short read.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Reads a signed short into `scount` and rejects negative counts with a log.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Casts `scount` to `tcount`.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Adds a second check `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf_size < ofs + [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m + tcount * [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to guard the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubsequent loop over entries.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The relevant diff [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext lines simplified[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```diff[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -    tcount = [0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned int[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35mexif_get_short[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf + ofs + [0m[1;36m14[0m[39m, d->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf_size < [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m + tcount * [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mbuf_size < [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mofs + [0m[1;36m16[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Short MakerNote"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        return;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        int scount = [0m[1;35mexif_get_sshort[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf + ofs + [0m[1;36m14[0m[39m, d->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mscount < [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Negative MakerNote count"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            return;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        tcount = [0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned int[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m scount;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mbuf_size < [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mofs + [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m + [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mtcount * [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"MakerNote entries overflow"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        return;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ofs += [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After rebuilding and re-running the fuzzer, the same AddressSanitizer error is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39memitted, now pointing at the patched code’s `exif_get_sshort` call [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m120[0m[39m in the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatched file[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Post-Patch Observations**  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The first check [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`buf_size < ofs + [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m does not guarantee that `buf + ofs + [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m14[0m[39m` and the two bytes read by `exif_get_sshort` lie within bounds. In particular, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif `buf_size == ofs + [0m[1;36m15[0m[39m`, the code proceeds into the signed-read block and still [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreads past the end.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash log is effectively identical to the initial run, highlighting that [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe unsafe read location was not fully protected by the new checks.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Areas for Further Investigation**  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Review and strengthen the boundary condition before calling [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mexif_get_sshort[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf + ofs + [0m[1;36m14[0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`: ensure at least [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes are available at that [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffset [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., check `buf_size >= ofs + [0m[1;36m14[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mshort[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Audit other code paths in `exif-mnote-data-apple.c` for similar offset [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marithmetic issues [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparticularly around subsequent tag parsing loops[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Examine helper functions in `exif-utils.c` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_get_sshort`, [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_get_short`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to understand their behavior on under-sized buffers and whether [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthey need internal protection or documented preconditions.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Consider a more holistic review of MakerNote loaders in libexif for consistent[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidation of tag counts, offsets, and data lengths.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is an AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow detected when the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mApple MakerNote loader [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_mnote_data_apple_load`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m calls `exif_get_sshort` past [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe end of its input buffer. The overflow occurs at offset [0m[1;36m14[0m[39m within a [0m[1;36m512[0m[39m-byte [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregion. A patch attempt was made in `libexif/apple/exif-mnote-data-apple.c` to add [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexplicit checks before reading the signed [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-bit count and before iterating over [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentries. After applying that patch, the same overflow in `exif_get_sshort` still [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moccurs at the same buffer address, indicating that the new checks did not prevent [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe out-of-bounds read.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer exercised `exif_from_data_fuzzer`, which loads EXIF data via [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_new_from_data` → `exif_data_load_data` → `exif_mnote_data_apple_load`.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Inside `exif_mnote_data_apple_load`, the code calls `[0m[1;35mexif_get_short[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf + ofs [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ [0m[1;36m14[0m[39m, d->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` without verifying that `ofs + [0m[1;36m14[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m` is within `buf_size`.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer reports a one-byte read heap-buffer-overflow at `buf + ofs + [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m14[0m[39m` when `buf_size` is [0m[1;36m512[0m[39m and the code attempts to read at offset [0m[1;36m517[0m[39m.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Important Observations  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow happens in `exif_get_sshort` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maliased by `exif_get_short`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreading two bytes beyond a [0m[1;36m512[0m[39m-byte allocation.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The buffer is allocated exactly to the size of the fuzzer input, so no [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madditional slack exists for red-zone.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The reported call stack pins the problem in `exif_mnote_data_apple_load`.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `exif-mnote-data-apple.c`, before reading the count at `ofs + [0m[1;36m14[0m[39m`, the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch inserted:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mbuf_size < [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mofs + [0m[1;36m14[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mshort[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Short MakerNote"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It then reads `scount = [0m[1;35mexif_get_sshort[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf + ofs + [0m[1;36m14[0m[39m, d->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` guarded by [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma non-negative check and casts to unsigned `tcount`.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A second check was added before advancing into the tag loop:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mbuf_size < [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mofs + [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m + [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mtcount * [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"MakerNote entries overflow"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This patch compiles and runs, but the same ASan report appears, showing the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow at the same address.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Post-Patch Log  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer run still reports:[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ==ERROR: AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow on address [0m[1;36m0x515000000785[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     READ of size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m at [0m[1;36m0x515000000785[0m[39m thread T0[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       #[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m  exif_get_sshort [0m[35m/src/libexif/libexif/[0m[95mexif-utils.c[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       #[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m  exif_get_short [0m[35m/src/libexif/libexif/[0m[95mexif-utils.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m104[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       #[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m  exif_mnote_data_apple_load [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/src/libexif/libexif/apple/[0m[95mexif-mnote-data-apple.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m120[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[33m...[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m0x515000000785[0m[39m is located [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m bytes after [0m[1;36m512[0m[39m-byte region [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x515000000580[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x515000000780[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The checks in `exif-mnote-data-apple.c` did not intercept this out-of-bounds [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mread.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The logic in `exif_mnote_data_apple_load` that computes `ofs` and the base [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds for the Apple MakerNote block. Ensure `ofs` is validated against `buf_size` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore any reads.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How `buf_size` is passed into `exif_mnote_data_apple_load`—is it the full data[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize or just the MakerNote segment?  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Whether integer overflow or signed/unsigned comparisons are causing the bounds[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks to be bypassed.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Other calls to `exif_get_short`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`exif_get_sshort` in this loader and related [0m  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libFuzzer run on the `exif_from_data_fuzzer` target uncovered a [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow in the `exif_get_sshort` call within [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_mnote_data_apple_load` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `libexif/apple/exif-mnote-data-apple.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. An [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempted patch added more rigorous boundary checks and replaced `exif_get_short` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith `exif_get_sshort`, but after applying it the code fails to compile with [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnumerous “undeclared identifier” and syntax errors in that same source file.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Fuzzer output indicates an AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow in [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_get_sshort` called from `exif_mnote_data_apple_load`.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• The overflow occurs because the code reads one byte past a [0m[1;36m512[0m[39m-byte allocation [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`READ of size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m at [0m[1;36m0x[0m[39m…[0m[1;36m785[0m[39m` while buffer ends at `…[0m[1;36m780[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Stack trace shows this path:  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  – `exif_mnote_data_apple_load` → `exif_data_load_data` → [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_new_from_data` → fuzzer entry.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• The problematic region is in `libexif/libexif/exif-utils.c` but triggered by [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmalformed MakerNote handling in the Apple-specific loader.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Modified `exif-mnote-data-apple.c`:  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  – Changed the early null-and-length check to separate checks for `d`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`buf` and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthen validate `buf_size` against a computed start offset.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  – Introduced a local block computing `start = d->offset + [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m`, checked `start + [0m[1;36m14[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<= buf_size`, then assigned `ofs = [0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned int[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mstart`.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  – Swapped `exif_get_short` for `exif_get_sshort` to detect negative counts, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogged and returned on `scount < [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m`.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  – Checked that `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mofs + [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m + tcount * [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m <= buf_size` before proceeding.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mResult of Applying Patch  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Compilation errors in `apple/exif-mnote-data-apple.c`:  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  – Numerous “use of undeclared identifier” errors for `buf`, `ofs`, `d`, and [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tcount`.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  – Syntax errors where C constructs or variable declarations went out of scope or [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwere missing entirely.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  – Implicit-int warnings and brace mismatches.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• The patch as applied has mis-scoped or omitted critical variable declarations and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbraces, so none of the new logic compiles.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• The function signature and local variable declarations in [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_mnote_data_apple_load` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparticularly `buf`, `buf_size`, `d`, `ofs`, [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tcount`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Ensure any new code is inserted within the correct scope and after all [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnecessary variables are declared.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• The original bounds and offset calculations around the MakerNote header and entry[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcount. Confirm how `d->offset`, `buf_size`, and indexing interact throughout the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• The use of `exif_get_sshort` vs. `exif_get_short`—verify that the signed variant [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis available and correctly declared in scope.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Surrounding code that allocates and uses the buffer to see if additional [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvariants or length checks are required prior to calling into `exif_utils.c`.[0m      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmp_jrql_kk[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzing harness `exif_from_data_fuzzer` repeatedly fed a [0m[1;36m512[0m[39m-byte input to the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mApple MakerNote loader in libexif. AddressSanitizer flagged a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow in exif_get_sshort [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcalled via exif_get_short[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when reading [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes at `buf + ofs + [0m[1;36m14[0m[39m` without ensuring that those two bytes existed. The [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubmitted patch in `exif-mnote-data-apple.c` added null checks, validated that the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m14[0m[39m-byte header fits, checked for negative entry counts, and ensured that `tcount * [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m` entries/trailer fit within `buf_size`. However, after applying the patch, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe same overflow at exif_get_sshort persisted, indicating that the new checks [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstill allow an out-of-bounds read.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer ran `exif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer reported a heap-buffer-overflow reading [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m byte at address [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;36m0x515000000785[0m[39m`, which is [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m bytes past the end of a [0m[1;36m512[0m[39m-byte allocation [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x[0m[39m…[0m[1;36m580[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x[0m[39m…[0m[1;36m780[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The invalid read occurs in exif_get_sshort [0m[1;39m([0m[39min exif-utils.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, invoked by [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_get_short, called from `exif_mnote_data_apple_load` in [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`libexif/apple/exif-mnote-data-apple.c`.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The backtrace shows that `ofs` was computed as `d->offset + [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m`, then `buf + [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mofs + [0m[1;36m14[0m[39m` was passed to exif_get_short without confirming that `ofs + [0m[1;36m14[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m < [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuf_size`.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Important observations  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The vulnerable code path executes when the MakerNote header is at least [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpartially present but too short to contain the [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m-byte count field and/or subsequent[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentries.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow is deterministic on a [0m[1;36m512[0m[39m-byte buffer with `d->offset` near the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mend of the buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround [0m[1;36m506[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - exif_get_sshort unconditionally reads two bytes, so any call where only one or[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mzero bytes remain triggers a heap OOB.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Location: `libexif/apple/exif-mnote-data-apple.c`, function [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_mnote_data_apple_load`.  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added at the top:  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Null checks for `d` and `buf`.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Computation of `size_t start = d->offset + [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m`; guard `start + [0m[1;36m14[0m[39m > [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuf_size`.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replaced the unguarded `tcount = [0m[1;35mexif_get_short[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf + ofs + [0m[1;36m14[0m[39m, d->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith:  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `int scount = [0m[1;35mexif_get_sshort[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf + ofs + [0m[1;36m14[0m[39m, d->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Early return if `scount < [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m`.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Cast to unsigned `tcount = [0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m scount`.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Guard `[0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mofs + [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m + tcount * [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m > buf_size`.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The logging messages were adjusted to differentiate missing data, header too [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshort, negative count, and entry overflow.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Post-patch result  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer run still triggers the same AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat exif_get_sshort in the same code path.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The failure backtrace now points to line [0m[1;36m121[0m[39m in `exif-mnote-data-apple.c`, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating that the two-byte read at `buf + ofs + [0m[1;36m14[0m[39m` remains unguarded in certain [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode paths.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for further investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The precise value of `ofs` and whether the `start + [0m[1;36m14[0m[39m` check is correctly [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcovering all scenarios where `d->offset + [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m14[0m[39m` might overflow.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The cast of `start` to `unsigned int ofs` and possible truncation when [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`d->offset + [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m` exceeds `UINT_MAX`.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any additional code paths in `exif-mnote-data-apple.c` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor other MakerNote [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloaders[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that call exif_get_short/sshort without proper bounds checks.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The implementation of exif_get_sshort/exif_get_short in `exif-utils.c` to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munderstand its assumptions about buffer length.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overall handling of `d->offset` and `buf_size` across the EXIF parsing [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpipeline, including calls in `exif_data_load_data` and `exif_data_new_from_data`.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
